Sentencas: A solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with a liquid antimony anode (LAA) is a potential energy conversion technology for the use of impurity-containing fuels.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of atmospheric plasma sprayed solid oxide fuel cells with liquid antimony anodes

Sentencas: Atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) technology has become a promising LAA-SOFC preparation method because of its economy and convenience.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of atmospheric plasma sprayed solid oxide fuel cells with liquid antimony anodes

Sentencas: In this paper, button SOFCs with different cathode materials and ratios of pore former were prepared by the APS method and were operated at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of atmospheric plasma sprayed solid oxide fuel cells with liquid antimony anodes

Sentencas: The effect of the cathode structure on the electrochemical performance of the LAA-SOFCs was analyzed, and an optimized spraying method for LAA-SOFCs was developed.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of atmospheric plasma sprayed solid oxide fuel cells with liquid antimony anodes

Sentencas: A tubular LAA-SOFC was prepared using the APS method based on the optimized spraying method, and a peak power of 2.5 W was reached.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of atmospheric plasma sprayed solid oxide fuel cells with liquid antimony anodes

Sentencas: The tubular cell was also measured at a constant current of 2 A for 20 h and was fed with a sulfur-containing fuel to demonstrate its impurity resistance and electrode stability.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of atmospheric plasma sprayed solid oxide fuel cells with liquid antimony anodes
